remarks: "Cesaro", one of the syllogisms of Aristotelian logic.  No ` ph ` is ` ps ` , all ` ch ` is ` ps ` , and ` ch ` exist, therefore some ` ch ` is not ` ph ` .  (In Aristotelian notation, EAO-2:  PeM and SaM therefore SoP.) (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 28-Aug-2016.) (Revised by David A. Wheeler, 2-Sep-2016.)
statement:
cesaro.maj $e |- A. x ( ph -> -. ps ) $.
cesaro.min $e |- A. x ( ch -> ps ) $.
cesaro.e $e |- E. x ch $.
cesaro $p |- E. x ( ch /\ -. ph ) $.
